#Day 3

## Age Group Analysis

Average claim amounts varied across age groups.

| Age Group | Average Claim Amount |
| --------- | -------------------- |
| 15-25     | 53,873               |
| 25-35     | 50,361               |
| 35-45     | 52,996               |
| 45-55     | 54,721               |
| 55+       | 58,997               |

### Key Observation

Policyholders aged 55+ exhibited the highest average claim amount, while the 25-35 age group showed the lowest average claim cost.


## Incident Severity Analysis

| Incident Severity | Average Claim Amount |
| ----------------- | -------------------- |
| Major Damage      | 64,067               |
| Total Loss        | 62,081               |
| Minor Damage      | 48,643               |
| Trivial Damage    | 5,302                |

### Key Observation

Incident severity was a major driver of claim costs. Major Damage and Total Loss incidents generated substantially higher claims than Minor or Trivial Damage incidents.


